1
00:00:08,040 --> 00:00:12,100
Episode 22

2
00:00:22,520 --> 00:00:24,540
I understand.

3
00:00:44,150 --> 00:00:46,100
Welcome.

4
00:01:16,840 --> 00:01:20,540
This is what you were looking for, isn't it?

5
00:01:20,540 --> 00:01:23,290
So you really brought it, huh?

6
00:01:23,290 --> 00:01:25,020
You didn't open that, did you?

7
00:01:25,020 --> 00:01:27,560
You told me not to.

8
00:01:27,560 --> 00:01:30,500
You really didn't open it because I asked you not to?

9
00:01:30,500 --> 00:01:32,330
You promised me.

10
00:01:32,330 --> 00:01:37,450
That if I didn't look at it, kept my mouth shut, and brought it to you without telling anyone,

11
00:01:38,820 --> 00:01:41,350
you would tell me who else was in that warehouse.

12
00:01:41,350 --> 00:01:44,710
Yes. I did promise that.

13
00:01:46,350 --> 00:01:49,470
Please don't ever come back to our flower shop.

14
00:01:49,470 --> 00:01:52,020
I won't go there either.

15
00:01:59,240 --> 00:02:00,270
So please tell me now.

16
00:02:00,270 --> 00:02:05,840
Who was in that warehouse that day, along with me and Kim Ian?

17
00:02:05,840 --> 00:02:08,350
Do you like old songs, by any chance?

18
00:02:08,350 --> 00:02:09,990
Huh?

19
00:02:33,810 --> 00:02:35,760
♫ When are you gonna come down? ♫

20
00:02:35,760 --> 00:02:39,090
My mother listened to this song often.
(Elton John's "Goodbye Yellow Brick Road")

21
00:02:39,090 --> 00:02:40,900
Just give me the answer already!

22
00:02:40,900 --> 00:02:45,400
- You said you would tell me who else was there.
- Did I?

23
00:02:45,400 --> 00:02:48,140
You said you would tell me.

24
00:02:49,300 --> 00:02:50,690
I changed my mind.

25
00:02:50,690 --> 00:02:53,950
If I don't tell you, I think I will get more money later.

26
00:02:53,950 --> 00:02:57,100
Ahjussi, why do you live your life this way?

27
00:02:57,100 --> 00:02:59,700
I brought this to you because you said you would tell me.

28
00:02:59,700 --> 00:03:02,880
I even deceived someone that I like to bring you this...

29
00:03:02,880 --> 00:03:06,440
Who? Jang Yun?

30
00:03:07,290 --> 00:03:10,230
It not my fault that I live my life this way.

31
00:03:10,230 --> 00:03:14,750
The world has made me this way. I've been victimized a lot, you see.

32
00:03:14,750 --> 00:03:18,780
So I am prepared, leaving something as an insurance

33
00:03:18,780 --> 00:03:21,080
and hide it in a place I like.

34
00:03:21,100 --> 00:03:25,600
So when bastards stab me in the back, I have something to use.

35
00:03:25,680 --> 00:03:26,860
Don't make me laugh.

36
00:03:26,860 --> 00:03:32,980
The reason you lie and steal money from people is all your own fault, Ahjussi.

37
00:03:33,680 --> 00:03:35,430
How naive.

38
00:03:35,430 --> 00:03:37,990
You're just saying that because you don't know the real world.

39
00:03:37,990 --> 00:03:41,970
Do you know how dirty and vulgar the world is?

40
00:03:41,970 --> 00:03:45,970
I may not know, but I know that you are a liar.

41
00:03:47,360 --> 00:03:48,990
Don't worry.

42
00:03:48,990 --> 00:03:51,940
Even I will want to do something good before I die.

43
00:03:51,940 --> 00:03:54,710
If I happen to die, look for it.

44
00:03:54,710 --> 00:03:57,900
I may have left behind a gift for you.

45
00:03:57,900 --> 00:04:00,640
Don't play around with people like this.

46
00:04:02,940 --> 00:04:05,880
Please don't appear in front of my family again.

47
00:04:05,880 --> 00:04:10,960
If you do, I will go to the police station to tell them everything that has happened.

48
00:04:12,280 --> 00:04:15,020
♫ It'll take you a couple of vodka ♫

49
00:04:15,020 --> 00:04:16,830
Don't forget what I said, Yi Yeong.

50
00:04:16,830 --> 00:04:20,630
♫ To set you on your feet again ♫

51
00:04:20,630 --> 00:04:24,640
♫ Maybe you'll get a replacement ♫

52
00:04:24,640 --> 00:04:28,590
♫ There's plenty like me to be found ♫

53
00:04:40,870 --> 00:04:43,700
Where did you go so late?

54
00:04:45,510 --> 00:04:47,550
The convenience store.

55
00:04:47,550 --> 00:04:49,900
This late?

56
00:04:49,900 --> 00:04:51,520
Yes.

57
00:04:55,540 --> 00:04:59,390
Why weren't you sleeping? Tomorrow is an important day.

58
00:05:00,160 --> 00:05:03,940
Just... I can't sleep.

59
00:05:07,870 --> 00:05:10,820
I feel as if I haven't seen you for a while.

60
00:05:10,820 --> 00:05:13,540
Although I managed to run into you, right?

61
00:05:17,730 --> 00:05:19,350
Yes.

62
00:05:24,420 --> 00:05:26,420
Sorry.

63
00:05:31,040 --> 00:05:37,370
Yesterday and today, I felt a bit helpless.

64
00:05:40,740 --> 00:05:43,900
I feel like there isn't anything I can do.

65
00:05:45,300 --> 00:05:47,630
So I was a bit frustrated.

66
00:05:53,310 --> 00:05:55,640
I was out here, hoping that I could see you, even briefly.

67
00:05:55,640 --> 00:05:57,700
Go on in, sleep well.

68
00:06:01,910 --> 00:06:04,450
I'm sorry, too.

69
00:06:07,820 --> 00:06:10,570
I'm really very sorry.

70
00:06:36,190 --> 00:06:38,480
Everything happened because of you.

71
00:06:38,480 --> 00:06:40,580
Kim Ian died because of you.

72
00:06:40,580 --> 00:06:46,010
And Hong Yi Yeong's life became messed up because of you.

73
00:06:46,010 --> 00:06:50,360
What did you give in exchange for the conductor's post?

74
00:07:07,630 --> 00:07:11,880
Is that why you killed Ian?
Phone call from Y

75
00:07:16,730 --> 00:07:18,710
What is the gift you said you had for me?

76
00:07:18,710 --> 00:07:21,690
Did you find the item, by any chance?

77
00:07:22,460 --> 00:07:25,020
You are so impatient.

78
00:07:25,020 --> 00:07:30,440
I did. If you give me the promised money first, I will give it to you.

79
00:07:32,330 --> 00:07:34,510
This bastard...

80
00:07:35,460 --> 00:07:38,960
I don't know if you really found it, or even what you found.

81
00:07:38,960 --> 00:07:41,780
How can I trust you and give you money?

82
00:07:46,010 --> 00:07:47,280
Give it to me.

83
00:07:47,280 --> 00:07:48,680
Give it, you bastard!

84
00:07:48,680 --> 00:07:51,370
This bastard! Give it!

85
00:07:53,080 --> 00:07:56,860
I didn't look at it, as I promised you, Professor.

86
00:07:56,860 --> 00:07:59,400
You bastard...

87
00:08:00,930 --> 00:08:01,790
This bastard...

88
00:08:01,790 --> 00:08:04,400
If you don't give me the money, I will look at it.

89
00:08:04,400 --> 00:08:06,770
When will you give it to me?

90
00:08:09,610 --> 00:08:11,300
Fine.

91
00:08:11,300 --> 00:08:17,500
I will give you half and the rest after you take care of just one guy.

92
00:08:17,500 --> 00:08:20,050
Who?

93
00:08:20,050 --> 00:08:21,460
Nam Ju Wan.

94
00:08:21,460 --> 00:08:26,350
Crush him just to the verge of death, so he can't babble in front of me ever again.

95
00:08:26,350 --> 00:08:31,390
I pulled and raised that guy up and defended and shielded him, and what?

96
00:08:33,390 --> 00:08:34,750
Why are you laughing?

97
00:08:34,750 --> 00:08:37,150
Because it's funny.

98
00:08:37,150 --> 00:08:39,640
You people are like that, of course.

99
00:08:45,190 --> 00:08:46,370
Where are you going, you bastard?

100
00:08:46,370 --> 00:08:48,660
Are you crazy?

101
00:08:49,590 --> 00:08:52,510
I think I changed my mind, Professor.

102
00:08:52,510 --> 00:08:54,800
I want to keep this item.

103
00:08:54,800 --> 00:08:59,420
There are a lot of people who want this besides you.

104
00:09:02,250 --> 00:09:05,020
How can you just leave, you bastard?

105
00:09:15,510 --> 00:09:19,130
If we see each other so often, we might develop affection for each other.

106
00:09:19,960 --> 00:09:22,790
So what brings you here today?

107
00:09:22,790 --> 00:09:24,200
I have a request.

108
00:09:24,200 --> 00:09:27,300
A request? For me?

109
00:09:27,300 --> 00:09:30,130
Please tell me what happened that day.

110
00:09:30,130 --> 00:09:35,940
I'm not asking you to do anything. I just want to know what happened that day.

111
00:09:37,230 --> 00:09:39,490
You didn't kill Ian, did you?

112
00:09:39,490 --> 00:09:42,950
I told you, it wasn't me.

113
00:09:42,950 --> 00:09:44,460
You finally believe me.

114
00:09:44,460 --> 00:09:46,700
Then who killed him? And why?

115
00:09:46,700 --> 00:09:50,590
And why does Hong Yi Yeong think she stabbed Ian?

116
00:09:50,590 --> 00:09:53,520
Please tell me, I ask of you.

117
00:09:53,520 --> 00:09:55,160
Jang Yun,

118
00:09:55,160 --> 00:09:58,810
I mean, Jang Do Hun, you have to being me money.

119
00:09:58,810 --> 00:10:01,540
Then I will tell you, won't I?

120
00:10:01,540 --> 00:10:04,970
So I will give it to you, I will find a way, somehow.

121
00:10:04,970 --> 00:10:07,920
But it will take time.

122
00:10:07,920 --> 00:10:10,190
Then come when you do that.

123
00:10:12,440 --> 00:10:16,270
Please, I'm begging. I will make sure to keep my promise.

124
00:10:16,270 --> 00:10:18,350
Promise?

125
00:10:20,720 --> 00:10:23,300
Let me tell you just one thing.

126
00:10:23,300 --> 00:10:26,900
This is no longer a secret, anyway.

127
00:10:27,910 --> 00:10:33,580
Hong Yi Yeong is not the one who killed Kim Ian.

128
00:10:34,690 --> 00:10:39,110
He was stabbed, but that wasn't why he died.

129
00:10:39,110 --> 00:10:41,800
Someone else is the murderer.

130
00:10:41,800 --> 00:10:45,800
So who is that? I'm asking who it is.

131
00:10:45,820 --> 00:10:49,280
That's all I can tell you right now.

132
00:10:49,280 --> 00:10:51,990
Bring me the money.

133
00:10:51,990 --> 00:10:56,030
Then I will tell you the next thing.

134
00:11:13,780 --> 00:11:18,990
No Entry / Rehearsal

135
00:11:20,750 --> 00:11:22,470
Everyone has worked hard.

136
00:11:22,470 --> 00:11:24,740
Lunch boxes will be passed out in 30 minutes.

137
00:11:24,740 --> 00:11:28,950
Please don't leave the building if possible and stand by in the waiting room.

138
00:11:28,950 --> 00:11:31,270
Yes.

139
00:11:31,270 --> 00:11:33,540
My belly hurts.

140
00:11:33,540 --> 00:11:35,480
Oh no, I think I have indigestion.

141
00:11:35,480 --> 00:11:38,270
Again? Do you want medicine?

142
00:11:38,270 --> 00:11:42,410
Medicine is useless. This always happens before a performance.

143
00:11:42,410 --> 00:11:46,690
Every time I went on stage earlier in my career, I always vomited.

144
00:11:46,690 --> 00:11:50,170
I had one shot of soju every day.

145
00:11:50,170 --> 00:11:52,410
Huh?

146
00:12:12,710 --> 00:12:16,110
The rehearsal went well, I've got a good feeling.

147
00:12:17,490 --> 00:12:20,080
Did you have dinner?

148
00:12:20,080 --> 00:12:23,630
I don't have any appetite. What do you need?

149
00:12:23,630 --> 00:12:26,220
To please take care of us well today.

150
00:12:26,220 --> 00:12:29,530
The future of our orchestra is in your hands.

151
00:12:29,530 --> 00:12:31,520
Why do you say that all of a sudden?

152
00:12:31,520 --> 00:12:37,040
Even if you hear some unpleasant rumor, don't pay much attention.

153
00:12:37,040 --> 00:12:41,870
Whatever happens, I will somehow find a way to be your shield.

154
00:12:41,870 --> 00:12:43,800
Got that?

155
00:12:45,320 --> 00:12:47,560
I've got no one but you, Sunbae.

156
00:12:49,420 --> 00:12:51,720
Good luck.

157
00:13:02,350 --> 00:13:04,580
Conductor, we're here.

158
00:13:04,580 --> 00:13:07,680
Granny is here, too.

159
00:13:07,680 --> 00:13:09,940
My Ms. Bok Bun, you are dressed so pretty.

160
00:13:09,940 --> 00:13:13,970
Oh, my baby.

161
00:13:16,740 --> 00:13:20,870
But what's with your face?

162
00:13:20,870 --> 00:13:22,700
Didn't you sleep well?

163
00:13:22,700 --> 00:13:26,270
I couldn't sleep because I was so excited to see Ms. Bok Bun.

164
00:13:26,270 --> 00:13:28,760
This crazy boy.

165
00:13:28,760 --> 00:13:32,030
President Go offered to personally show her around today.

166
00:13:32,030 --> 00:13:34,390
He wants me to do some work, that is.

167
00:13:35,140 --> 00:13:37,010
Look around.

168
00:13:39,560 --> 00:13:41,340
The phone number you have called ...

169
00:13:41,340 --> 00:13:43,970
This man, he's not answering the phone since yesterday.

170
00:13:43,970 --> 00:13:45,670
Is he sick or something?

171
00:13:45,670 --> 00:13:48,420
Who? Yeong Gil?

172
00:13:49,480 --> 00:13:54,270
I had a lot of deliveries, so I was waiting to ask him to do some.

173
00:13:54,270 --> 00:13:58,090
I guess he has a situation. Try calling him again tomorrow.

174
00:13:58,090 --> 00:14:00,660
I will do all the work for you.

175
00:14:01,550 --> 00:14:05,760
He is ten times faster than you are.

176
00:14:05,760 --> 00:14:10,900
Our Su Yeong shouldn't be late to the concert.

177
00:14:10,900 --> 00:14:15,590
Knowing her, I'm afraid she will finally arrive when the concert is over.

178
00:14:15,590 --> 00:14:17,780
Did you send the flowers?

179
00:14:17,780 --> 00:14:21,520
Of course. It's Conductor's first performance.

180
00:14:21,520 --> 00:14:23,710
But we have so much backed up work, now of all times.

181
00:14:23,710 --> 00:14:26,400
Will he be sad?

182
00:14:26,400 --> 00:14:27,890
I'm sure he understands.

183
00:14:27,890 --> 00:14:31,680
When he hangs out with our Yi Yeong later, we can go see him then.

184
00:14:31,680 --> 00:14:34,910
But still, that's that, and this is this.

185
00:14:34,910 --> 00:14:40,020
This won't do. I will try calling him again.

186
00:14:40,020 --> 00:14:43,420
Flower Shop

187
00:14:43,420 --> 00:14:48,850
♫ Hunting the horny-back toad ♫

188
00:14:48,850 --> 00:14:53,760
♫ Oh I've finally decided my future lies ♫

189
00:14:53,760 --> 00:14:56,370
♫ Beyond the yellow brick road ♫

190
00:14:56,370 --> 00:14:59,040
Going to confess your feelings?

191
00:15:00,870 --> 00:15:02,960
Well, something like that.

192
00:15:05,210 --> 00:15:07,260
Thank you.

193
00:15:07,260 --> 00:15:09,210
Goodbye.

194
00:15:23,450 --> 00:15:25,780
You look cool today.

195
00:15:28,900 --> 00:15:32,120
You're not trembling, or anything, are you?

196
00:15:32,920 --> 00:15:35,430
I usually don't tremble about things like this.

197
00:15:35,430 --> 00:15:37,880
How nice for you.

198
00:15:41,690 --> 00:15:43,680
Have a good performance.

199
00:15:43,680 --> 00:15:47,180
It's alright if you make a mistake, so don't be nervous.

200
00:15:47,180 --> 00:15:50,810
I'm not even the main player, so I just have to do what I always did.

201
00:15:50,810 --> 00:15:56,590
It's the same as the main role.  When you play the first encore ...

202
00:16:09,900 --> 00:16:12,070
Oh, so shocking.

203
00:16:12,980 --> 00:16:14,490
Who are you?

204
00:16:14,490 --> 00:16:16,660
Is Conductor in there?

205
00:16:16,660 --> 00:16:20,750
He's not here right now.

206
00:16:20,750 --> 00:16:24,300
But no one can come in here unless they are associates.

207
00:16:24,300 --> 00:16:27,160
How did you get in?

208
00:16:27,890 --> 00:16:30,280
By walking.

209
00:16:30,280 --> 00:16:33,370
Please give this to the Conductor.

210
00:16:35,390 --> 00:16:37,630
I hope his performance goes well.

211
00:16:37,630 --> 00:16:41,720
There is a place to accept gifts in the lobby.

212
00:16:41,720 --> 00:16:45,030
Who shall I say this is from?

213
00:16:45,030 --> 00:16:46,890
A fan.

214
00:17:21,360 --> 00:17:24,660
What do you want? The performance will begin soon.

215
00:17:24,660 --> 00:17:27,320
I found the item.

216
00:17:27,320 --> 00:17:30,780
I called you yesterday, but you didn't answer.

217
00:17:30,780 --> 00:17:33,730
Is that it? That's why you called before the performance?

218
00:17:33,730 --> 00:17:38,500
'Is that it?' But someone died because of that.

219
00:17:38,500 --> 00:17:40,070
Let's talk after the performance.

220
00:17:40,070 --> 00:17:44,790
Do you know who found that for me?

221
00:17:46,350 --> 00:17:48,560
Hong Yi Yeong.

222
00:18:03,130 --> 00:18:05,500
He's not in his room and we can't find him anywhere.

223
00:18:05,500 --> 00:18:08,090
He hasn't changed his clothes yet.

224
00:18:08,900 --> 00:18:12,500
- How many minutes are left?
- 15 minutes.

225
00:18:12,530 --> 00:18:17,140
Let's split up and look again. And just in case, let's look backstage, too.

226
00:18:18,000 --> 00:18:21,500
Be careful so that the orchestra members don't find out. They shouldn't find out.

227
00:18:21,500 --> 00:18:23,190
Yes.

228
00:18:25,210 --> 00:18:27,130
This way.

229
00:18:28,130 --> 00:18:30,250
Yi Yeong?

230
00:18:30,250 --> 00:18:34,330
If her memory hasn't returned... did you threaten her or something?

231
00:18:34,400 --> 00:18:39,400
Threats? No.  It was a deal.

232
00:18:39,400 --> 00:18:43,720
Hong Yi Yeong asked me to tell her what happened that day, last year.

233
00:18:43,720 --> 00:18:45,690
So I thew her a bait.

234
00:18:45,690 --> 00:18:51,000
That besides her and Kim Ian, there was someone else there.

235
00:18:52,340 --> 00:18:56,430
That if she brought me the item, I would tell her.

236
00:18:56,500 --> 00:19:00,600
And she really found it and brought it to me, naively.

237
00:19:00,600 --> 00:19:03,860
So, did you tell her?

238
00:19:03,900 --> 00:19:08,000
No, I held back.  Didn't I do well?

239
00:19:09,920 --> 00:19:16,350
If I want to sell this item to you, Conductor, then I can't tell her that name, can I?

240
00:19:20,000 --> 00:19:26,100
If you want the item, I will give it to you. You must pay me in exchange for it.

241
00:19:26,100 --> 00:19:29,690
How dare you come to this place to speak about money?

242
00:19:29,690 --> 00:19:32,440
So what is this place, anyway?

243
00:19:35,400 --> 00:19:39,200
The place where you will conduct? I  don't have anything to do with that.

244
00:19:39,200 --> 00:19:41,360
I don't have time, let's talk later.

245
00:19:41,360 --> 00:19:43,330
Later?

246
00:19:45,190 --> 00:19:47,380
There is no later.

247
00:19:49,010 --> 00:19:51,700
Professor Kang Myeong Seok offered me the rest of the money

248
00:19:51,700 --> 00:19:55,060
and he asked me to take care of you, just until you're almost dead.

249
00:19:55,060 --> 00:19:56,610
What?

250
00:19:56,610 --> 00:19:59,520
Really vulgar, isn't it?

251
00:19:59,520 --> 00:20:02,800
I really can't forgive you guys.

252
00:20:02,800 --> 00:20:05,830
Made me into a murderer, won't even give me money,

253
00:20:05,830 --> 00:20:09,900
acting high and mighty about your work, treat money like it's nothing, and treat me like trash.

254
00:20:09,900 --> 00:20:16,560
Professor Kang is trash, but you don't have the right to stand there, either.

255
00:20:17,270 --> 00:20:19,000
I've decided today.

256
00:20:19,000 --> 00:20:24,950
Professor Kang and you, I will destroy you, one by one.

257
00:20:25,660 --> 00:20:30,460
First is you. Who shall I tell everything to?

258
00:20:30,460 --> 00:20:33,410
Jang Yun? CEO Jang?

259
00:20:33,410 --> 00:20:35,530
Or the police?

260
00:20:37,370 --> 00:20:40,430
Conductor, conduct well.

261
00:20:42,740 --> 00:20:45,590
Today might be the last time.

262
00:21:42,040 --> 00:21:44,490
Where is he... ?

263
00:21:44,490 --> 00:21:46,790
Conductor.

264
00:21:47,540 --> 00:21:50,190
We've been looking for you for so long, where were you?

265
00:21:50,200 --> 00:21:54,700
Sorry.  Shall we go?

266
00:22:05,860 --> 00:22:08,400
Good luck, you'll do great.

267
00:22:15,680 --> 00:22:16,950
Yes, did you find him?

268
00:22:16,950 --> 00:22:21,090
He just went to the waiting room, he is getting dressed.

269
00:22:21,090 --> 00:22:24,390
He really makes me stressed until the last minute.

270
00:22:24,390 --> 00:22:26,340
Alright.

271
00:22:27,240 --> 00:22:29,420
Good luck.

272
00:22:38,680 --> 00:22:41,510
Conductor, are you alright?

273
00:22:41,510 --> 00:22:43,110
Yes.

274
00:22:46,510 --> 00:22:48,180
Conductor, please come out.

275
00:22:48,180 --> 00:22:50,410
Yes, he's coming.

276
00:23:05,040 --> 00:23:08,180
Hold on, I'll do that later.

277
00:23:08,180 --> 00:23:11,150
Even if you're feeling a bit overwhelmed, please bear it for a little while longer.

278
00:23:19,000 --> 00:23:23,200
Don't be too nervous.  You'll do well.

279
00:23:23,200 --> 00:23:25,970
Ms. Bok Bun is here, too.

280
00:24:55,360 --> 00:24:57,110
What's wrong?

281
00:30:11,240 --> 00:30:18,570
Timing and Subtitles by the Sing To Me Team @ viki

282
00:30:18,570 --> 00:30:25,740
♫ Even it is a brief moment, if I could call you ♫

283
00:30:25,740 --> 00:30:29,260
♫ I found myself but I’m still losing myself ♫

284
00:30:29,260 --> 00:30:32,610
♫ Can you come back to me? ♫

285
00:30:32,610 --> 00:30:37,590
♫ Because I can't forget, I cry. ♫

286
00:30:37,590 --> 00:30:40,230
I Wanna Hear Your Song Preview

287
00:30:40,230 --> 00:30:41,980
Bang, bang, bang bang!

288
00:30:41,980 --> 00:30:44,300
- You did well.
- What app is that?

289
00:30:44,300 --> 00:30:45,900
I hope you don't go in today.

290
00:30:45,900 --> 00:30:48,390
Someday we can stand on the same stage, right?

291
00:30:48,390 --> 00:30:51,350
Today at around 4 a.m, in the building of the Sinyeong Philharmonic ...

292
00:30:51,350 --> 00:30:53,040
Yes, we have nothing to do that, really.

293
00:30:53,040 --> 00:30:55,030
Maybe he was killed because of what I gave him?

294
00:30:55,030 --> 00:30:56,600
He asked me for money.

295
00:30:56,600 --> 00:30:58,570
I'm sure he asked the same of others.

296
00:30:58,570 --> 00:31:00,120
Please answer me now.

297
00:31:00,120 --> 00:31:02,660
What is your purpose for getting involved with Sinyeong Philharmonic, CEO Jang?

298
00:31:02,660 --> 00:31:06,670
Did you push him off the building? I saw you meet with Yun Yeong Gil.

299
00:31:06,670 --> 00:31:09,110
Just tell me. The truth will become known anyway.

300
00:31:09,110 --> 00:31:11,640
♫ If this is not end, when is the end? ♫

301
00:31:11,640 --> 00:31:13,000
♫ You are getting farther and farther away ♫
